    );
  }

  return reconstructed; // Reconstructed training sample
}
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Raw probability scores with high precision enable membership inference attacks
- Gradient exposure allows attackers to reconstruct training data
- Model architecture exposure enables model stealing and targeted attacks
- No rate limiting allows automated extraction campaigns

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const tf = require('@tensorflow/tfjs-node');
const crypto = require('crypto');

const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

let model;
const CONFIDENCE_PRECISION = 2;  // Limit decimal places
